'''''Golf's Best: St. Andrews - The Home of Golf''''' is a 1986 video game published by [[1 Step Software, Inc.]]

==Gameplay==
''Golf's Best'' is a game in which the Pinehurst course is included.<ref name="CGW29"/>

==Reception==
James Delson for ''[[Family Computing]]'' stated "Not for arcade aficionados who want lots of action, this is a thinking game for sports enthusiasts and serious gamers age 10 and over."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/family-computing-27/page/n103/mode/2up|title=Family Computing Magazine Issue 27|date=November 1985}}</ref>

Rick Teverbaugh reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "Golf's Best comes highly recommended from this duffer."<ref name="CGW29">{{cite magazine |last=Teverbaugh |first=Rick |title=Sports Scoreboard |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=Juneâ€“July 1986 |volume=1 |issue=29 |pages=32}}</ref>

Stephen Banker for ''[[Compute!]]'' described the game as "Among the cleverest" in arcade-style games based on contests of skill.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/1988-07-compute-magazine/page/n33/mode/2up|title = Compute! Magazine Issue 098|date = July 1988}}</ref>

